cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.HC 

This paper deals with analyzing and modeling consumer behavior using digital traces of shopping and purchases. It involves data analysis, machine learning, and social network analysis, which are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. Specifically, cs.CY (Computers and Society) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on understanding and predicting consumer behavior, which has implications for marketing and e-commerce. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) are also relevant as the paper involves social network analysis and building a predictive model. cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) is another possible category as the paper deals with consumer spending and its impact on the economy. Finally, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper aims to make online shopping more pleasant and efficient.
